  in the late 1920s , severance and van alen found themselves engaged in designing buildings that were heralded in the press to become the tallest buildings in the world :   severance , the manhattan trust building 40 wall street and van alen , the chrysler building .

living in nyc : architect william van alen put radiator caps on the 31st floor of this art deco landmark at 405 lexington

the chrysler building